sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant AEW as «view»<br>:AdminEventsWindow
    participant AEC as «controller»<br>:AdminEventController
    participant E as Event
    participant N as Notification

    note over Admin,N: USE CASE 1: CREATE EVENT
    Admin->>+AEW: fill new event details & submit
    AEW->>+AEC: store(request)
    AEC->>+E: create new event record
    E-->>-AEC: record created
    AEC-->>-AEW: return success redirect
    AEW-->>-Admin: display event created success message

    note over Admin,N: USE CASE 2: VIEW EVENT
    Admin->>+AEW: click to view event details
    AEW->>+AEC: show(id)
    AEC->>+E: get event details (id)
    E-->>-AEC: return event data
    AEC-->>-AEW: return view with event data
    AEW-->>-Admin: display event details

    note over Admin,N: USE CASE 3: EDIT EVENT
    Admin->>+AEW: modify event details & submit
    AEW->>+AEC: update(request, id)
    AEC->>+E: update event record
    E-->>-AEC: update confirmed
    
    AEC->>+N: notifyAllParticipants()
    N-->>-AEC: notifications sent
    
    AEC-->>-AEW: return success redirect
    AEW-->>-Admin: display updated event

    note over Admin,E: USE CASE 4: DELETE EVENT
    Admin->>+AEW: click delete event
    AEW->>+AEC: destroy(id)
    
    alt [Event has no dependencies]
        AEC->>+E: delete record
        E-->>-AEC: deletion confirmed
        AEC-->>-AEW: return success redirect
        AEW-->>-Admin: display deletion success
    else [Event has dependencies (e.g., participants)]
        AEC-->>AEW: return error redirect
        AEW-->>Admin: display cannot delete event with participants
    end
